<dec f='llvm/clang/include/clang-c/Index.h' l='4844' type='CXSourceRange clang_getCursorReferenceNameRange(CXCursor C, unsigned int NameFlags, unsigned int PieceIndex)'/>
<doc f='llvm/clang/include/clang-c/Index.h' l='4826'>/**
 * Given a cursor that references something else, return the source range
 * covering that reference.
 *
 * \param C A cursor pointing to a member reference, a declaration reference, or
 * an operator call.
 * \param NameFlags A bitset with three independent flags:
 * CXNameRange_WantQualifier, CXNameRange_WantTemplateArgs, and
 * CXNameRange_WantSinglePiece.
 * \param PieceIndex For contiguous names or when passing the flag
 * CXNameRange_WantSinglePiece, only one piece with index 0 is
 * available. When the CXNameRange_WantSinglePiece flag is not passed for a
 * non-contiguous names, this index can be used to retrieve the individual
 * pieces of the name. See also CXNameRange_WantSinglePiece.
 *
 * \returns The piece of the name pointed to by the given cursor. If there is no
 * name, or if the PieceIndex is out-of-range, a null-cursor will be returned.
 */</doc>
